The Telegraph - Calcutta

 $305 million sponsorship deal for Fifa 

London: Sony Corporation has signed a $305 million deal to become a sponsor of soccer?s world governing body Fifa from 2007 to 2014. 

The deal is the first global sponsorship agreement entered into by the Tokyo-based company and will join Adidas and Hyundai and three as yet unnamed companies as ?Fifa partners.? 

Under the terms of the deal, Sony will have ?core sponsorship rights? to all Fifa competitions over the seven years, most notably the World Cups of 2010, which will take place in South Africa, and 2014. (Reuters) 




